# FloodGuard — Style & Coding Standards

## Design System Color Tokens
Always use these Tailwind CSS custom tokens in classNames. Never use raw hex colors in className unless the value comes from a dynamic data array (use `style={{ color }}` for those).

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|---|---|---|
| `text-fg-cyan` / `border-fg-cyan` / `bg-fg-cyan` | `#00C8FF` | Primary accent, water, sensors, links |
| `text-fg-amber` / `border-fg-amber` | `#FFAA00` | Raspberry Pi, warnings, MEDIUM risk |
| `text-fg-purple` / `border-fg-purple` | `#C084FC` | ML/analytics, blockage events |
| `text-fg-green` / `border-fg-green` | `#00E676` | Success, LOW risk, gate closed, power |
| `text-fg-red` / `border-fg-red` | `#FF4444` | CRITICAL risk, danger, safety warnings |

## Tailwind CSS v4 Rules
- ✅ Use `bg-linear-to-r`, `bg-linear-to-br`, etc. for gradients
- ❌ NEVER use `bg-gradient-to-*` — deprecated in Tailwind v4

## Typography
- Headings: `font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground`
- Section labels: `font-mono tracking-[6px] text-fg-cyan/90 uppercase font-bold`
- Body: `text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed`
- Technical labels/values: `font-mono` class

## Component Patterns

### Cards
```tsx
<Card className="border-border/50 bg-card">
  <CardHeader className="pb-3 border-b border-border/40">
    <CardTitle className="text-lg text-fg-cyan">Title</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent className="p-5">...</CardContent>
</Card>
```

### Accent-colored card border (top line style)
```tsx
<div className="rounded-2xl border border-border/50 bg-card relative overflow-hidden">
  <div className="absolute top-0 inset-x-0 h-[2px]" style={{ background: color }} />
  ...
</div>
```

### Category filter buttons
```tsx
<button onClick={() => setFilter(cat)}
  className={cn(
    'text-sm font-mono px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full border transition-all',
    filter === cat
      ? 'bg-fg-amber/15 text-fg-amber border-fg-amber/40'
      : 'border-border/50 text-muted-foreground hover:border-fg-amber/30'
  )}>
  {cat}
</button>
```

### Section header with divider line
```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6 border-b border-border/50 pb-4">
  <Icon className="text-fg-cyan" size={24} />
  <h2 className="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">Section Title</h2>
</div>
```

## Animation Rules (Framer Motion)
- Page-level lists: `initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 24 }} whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }} viewport={{ once: true }}`
- Staggered rows: add `transition={{ delay: i * 0.05 }}`
- Hover lift: `whileHover={{ y: -4, transition: { duration: 0.2 } }}`
- Always use `motion.div` / `motion.tr` for animated elements

## File Organization
- All architecture tab data → `web/src/data/mockArchitectureData.ts`
- New tab components → defined as named functions ABOVE the default export in `architecture/page.tsx`
- Shared UI primitives → `web/src/components/ui/` (shadcn — do not edit)
- Global context → `web/src/context/ThemeProvider.tsx`

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (`PrototypeBuildTab`, `PhysicalTab`)
- Data arrays: camelCase (`bomItems`, `powerBudget`, `buildSteps`)
- Interfaces: PascalCase (`BOMItem`, `PowerEntry`, `ComponentSpec`)
- Files: kebab-case for routes (`page.tsx`, `FeaturesTab.tsx`)

## Key Don'ts
- ❌ Don't write `YF-S201` — the correct sensor is `YFS-401`
- ❌ Don't reference Flask — backend is FastAPI
- ❌ Don't reference SQLite — storage is Supabase
- ❌ Don't import `mockData` — import from `mockArchitectureData`
- ❌ Don't edit `src/components/ui/` files manually
- ❌ Don't use inline styles for layout — only for dynamic colors/values from data
